#Greetings

This application will say hello to either csci160 students or csci161 students,
then it will say goodbye to the same students


## Technologies

C++
gcc

## Build and Installation

Build:
There are 2 important make commands
"make all" 
"make clean"

"make all" will compile the necessary files and produce for you two exes in the bin folder
"make clean" will delete all files that were produced using the "make all" command

to compile and produce only one exe, type:
	make greetcsci160
		or
	make greetcsci161 
To install this application on linux
1) install github
	a) open mate terminal
	b) type: 
		apt-get install git-all
2) install Greetings
	a) open mate terminal
	b) Navigate to desired install location
        c) type:
		git clone https://github.com/Qoignis/csci161-lab1-upload.git
	d) if you wish to create a shortcut to your desktop, type:
		ln -s bin/greetcsci160 ~/Desktop
		ln -s bin/greetcsci161 ~/Desktop
type <install directory>/bin/greetcsci160 or <install directory>/bin/greetcsci161 to run program




## Usage

open Mate terminal
type 
	<install directory>/bin/greetcsci160
this will produce the message:
	Hello! CSCI 160
	Goodbye! CSCI 160
type
	<install directory>/bin/greetcsci161
this will produce the message:
	Hello! CSCI 161
	Goodbye! CSCI 161


